# First Client Checklist - ClawOps

## Purpose

This checklist ensures you're 100% ready to accept payment and deliver professional service. Going live before completing these items = amateur hour. Do it right.

**Timeline:** Complete everything BEFORE sending first proposal. Estimated total time: 12-16 hours spread over 3-5 days (accounting for verification delays).

---

## Phase 1: Legal & Financial Foundation (Must Complete First)

### Business Entity & Banking

- [ ] **Business entity registered** (LLC, sole proprietorship, etc.)
  - **Why:** Legal liability protection, tax benefits, professional credibility
  - **How:** LegalZoom ($300-500) or state website directly ($100-200)
  - **Timeline:** 1-2 weeks processing
  - **Status check:** Have EIN from IRS

- [ ] **Business bank account opened**
  - **Why:** Separate business/personal finances (required for legal protection)
  - **Recommended:** Chase Business, Mercury, Novo (online, fast approval)
  - **Requirements:** EIN, business formation docs, ID
  - **Timeline:** 2-7 days for approval
  - **Action:** Deposit $500 initial capital (for Stripe verification)

- [ ] **Business credit card obtained** (optional but recommended)
  - **Why:** Separates business expenses, builds credit, cash back on tools
  - **Recommended:** Chase Ink Business Cash (5% back on internet/phone), Amex Blue Business
  - **Timeline:** 7-10 days
  - **Alternative:** Use personal card initially, pay yourself back from business account

### Stripe Payment Processing

- [ ] **Stripe account created and verified**
  - **Account type:** Business (not personal)
  - **Business info:** Legal name, EIN, address, industry
  - **Identity verification:** Photo ID uploaded
  - **Status:** "Charges enabled" (not restricted)
  - **Timeline:** 1-3 business days for approval
  - **Red flag:** If restricted, resolve before first client

- [ ] **Bank account connected to Stripe**
  - **Verification method:** Micro-deposits (2-3 days) OR instant (Plaid)
  - **Payout schedule:** Daily (default) or weekly
  - **Test:** Verify routing/account numbers 3x (typo = delayed payouts)

- [ ] **Stripe products created**
  - [ ] Product 1: "ClawOps Starter" - $500/month subscription
  - [ ] Product 2: "ClawOps Growth" - $2,000/month subscription
  - [ ] Product 3: "Onboarding Fee" - $500 one-time (optional)
  - **Settings:** Tax collection enabled, email receipts on, failed payment retry enabled

- [ ] **Payment links generated**
  - [ ] Starter monthly: stripe.com/pay/[your-link]
  - [ ] Growth monthly: stripe.com/pay/[your-link]
  - **Test:** Click each link, verify pricing and description display correctly
  - **Bookmark:** Save links in password manager + email draft

- [ ] **Test payment completed**
  - **Test card:** 4242 4242 4242 4242, any future expiry, any CVC
  - **Verify:** Email receipt received, dashboard shows payment, refund works
  - **Then:** Refund test payment (don't pay fees for testing)

### Tax & Accounting Setup

- [ ] **Accounting software configured**
  - **Recommended:** QuickBooks Simple Start ($15/mo) or Wave (free but limited)
  - **Alternative:** Google Sheets with template (first 3 months only)
  - **Setup:** Link bank account, Stripe integration, expense categories

- [ ] **Sales tax collection enabled**
  - **Tool:** Stripe Tax (automatically calculates by state)
  - **Registration:** Not required until you hit state economic nexus thresholds
  - **Tracking:** Monitor when you approach $100K revenue in any state (register before hitting)

- [ ] **Tax estimated payment schedule set**
  - **Federal quarterly:** April 15, June 15, Sept 15, Jan 15
  - **State:** Check your state (usually matches federal)
  - **Estimate:** 25-30% of net profit (conservative)
  - **Action:** Set calendar reminders 30 days before each deadline

- [ ] **Business expense tracking system**
  - **Tool:** Expensify, QuickBooks mobile app, or Google Sheets
  - **Habit:** Photograph every receipt, categorize same day
  - **Categories:** Software/SaaS, marketing, office, meals (50% deductible), mileage

---

## Phase 2: Legal Contracts & Policies (Protect Yourself)

### Client Agreements

- [ ] **Master Service Agreement (MSA) template created**
  - **Source:** Bonsai ($24/mo for templates), LegalZoom, or lawyer ($500-1,500)
  - **Key clauses:**
    - Scope of services (what you do/don't do)
    - Payment terms (due dates, late fees)
    - Intellectual property (client owns deliverables)
    - Liability limitation (cap damages at fees paid)
    - Termination (30-day notice, what happens to data)
    - Confidentiality (mutual NDA)
    - Dispute resolution (arbitration, governing law)
  - **Format:** PDF + DocuSign/PandaDoc for e-signatures
  - **Test:** Send to friend to sign (verify workflow)

- [ ] **Statement of Work (SOW) template created**
  - **Purpose:** Specific deliverables per client (attached to MSA)
  - **Contents:** Project timeline, milestones, specific workflows, success metrics
  - **Why separate:** MSA is standard, SOW is custom per client
  - **Tip:** Don't start work until SOW signed (scope creep protection)

- [ ] **Terms of Service & Privacy Policy published**
  - **Location:** Website footer (required if collecting data)
  - **Generator:** Termly.io (free for basic), Iubenda ($27/mo)
  - **Key sections:** Service description, refund policy, data usage, cookies
  - **Compliance:** GDPR (if EU clients), CCPA (California), CAN-SPAM (emails)

### Insurance & Risk Management

- [ ] **Errors & Omissions (E&O) insurance purchased**
  - **Why:** Covers client lawsuits (e.g., "Your automation cost me $10K in lost sales")
  - **Cost:** $800-1,500/year for $1M coverage
  - **Providers:** Hiscox, Embroker, CoverWallet
  - **When:** BEFORE first client (seriously, don't skip)
  - **Alternative:** If can't afford, increase contract liability caps, require client insurance

- [ ] **General Liability insurance purchased** (optional)
  - **Why:** Covers property damage, bodily injury (less relevant for software)
  - **Cost:** $400-800/year
  - **When:** If meeting clients in person or operating from commercial space
  - **Skip if:** Fully remote, no physical interaction

### Data & Security Policies

- [ ] **Data handling procedures documented**
  - **Client data storage:** Where (AWS, Airtable, Google Drive), encryption, access controls
  - **API keys:** Never store in plain text, use environment variables, rotate quarterly
  - **Passwords:** 1Password or LastPass for team (if you hire)
  - **Backups:** Automated, encrypted, tested restore process

- [ ] **Security questionnaire template prepared**
  - **Why:** Enterprise clients will ask about security practices
  - **Topics:** Data encryption, access controls, incident response, compliance (SOC2, HIPAA if relevant)
  - **Template:** Google "SaaS security questionnaire template," adapt to your setup

---

## Phase 3: Client Onboarding System (Deliver Smoothly)

### Communication & Project Management

- [ ] **Business email domain configured**
  - **Format:** rick@clawops.com (not gmail.com)
  - **Tool:** Google Workspace ($15/mo) or Microsoft 365
  - **Setup:** Professional signature (name, title, phone, website, booking link)
  - **Test:** Send test emails, verify deliverability (not in spam)

- [ ] **Scheduling system set up**
  - **Tool:** Calendly (free) or SavvyCal ($12/mo, better UX)
  - **Event types:** 
    - Discovery call (30 min)
    - Onboarding kickoff (60 min)
    - Weekly check-in (30 min)
  - **Embed:** Link in email signature, website, proposals

- [ ] **Project management tool configured**
  - **Recommended:** Notion (free), ClickUp (free up to 5 clients), Trello
  - **Setup:** Template for client onboarding workflow
  - **Stages:** Signed → Kickoff → Discovery → Build → Test → Launch → Support
  - **Share:** Give each client view-only board (transparency builds trust)

- [ ] **CRM for lead tracking**
  - **Simple:** Google Sheets with columns: Name, Email, Status, Next Action, Value
  - **Better:** Airtable (free up to 1,200 records), HubSpot free tier
  - **Advanced:** Pipedrive ($15/mo, full sales pipeline)
  - **Must have:** Track every prospect, follow-up dates, win/loss reasons

### Onboarding Process & Materials

- [ ] **Welcome email template written**
  - **Subject:** "Welcome to ClawOps - Let's Get Started!"
  - **Contents:**
    - Thank you for trusting us
    - What happens next (kickoff call scheduled)
    - What we need from you (access, credentials, goals)
    - Who to contact (your email, phone)
    - Attach: SOW, invoice, onboarding checklist
  - **Tone:** Excited but professional, set expectations

- [ ] **Client onboarding checklist created**
  - **Shared doc:** Notion or Google Doc (checkboxes)
  - **Items:**
    - [ ] Kickoff call completed
    - [ ] Access granted (CRM, email, social accounts)
    - [ ] Goals & KPIs defined
    - [ ] Workflows prioritized
    - [ ] First automation built & tested
    - [ ] Training session completed
    - [ ] Client can run basic tasks independently
  - **Owner:** Both you and client check items (accountability)

- [ ] **Training materials prepared**
  - **Minimum:** Loom videos (5-10 min each) showing how to:
    - Monitor automation status
    - Review logs/reports
    - Request changes
    - Report issues
  - **Better:** Notion knowledge base with videos + written docs
  - **Best:** Interactive walkthrough (Intercom, WalkMe) but overkill for first client

- [ ] **Monthly reporting template created**
  - **Format:** PDF or Google Slides (visual > text)
  - **Sections:**
    - Automations executed (count, success rate)
    - Time saved (hours, dollar value)
    - Leads generated / emails sent / posts published (depending on service)
    - Issues resolved
    - Next month priorities
  - **Frequency:** Send 1st business day of each month (show value)

### Technical Infrastructure

- [ ] **Automation platform accounts set up**
  - **Required:** Make.com (Pro plan $15/mo minimum)
  - **Alternative:** Zapier (Starter $20/mo, easier for simple workflows)
  - **Setup:** Separate "organization" per client (isolates failures)
  - **Monitoring:** Email alerts for failed scenarios

- [ ] **AI API accounts created & funded**
  - [ ] OpenAI account: $50 prepaid (monitor usage)
  - [ ] Anthropic Claude: $50 prepaid
  - [ ] Usage limits: Set alerts at $30, hard cap at $100/month per client
  - **Billing:** Use business credit card (earn points, easier accounting)

- [ ] **Client workspace structure created**
  - **Folder system:**
    - `/clients/[client-name]/`
      - `/contracts/` (MSA, SOW, signed docs)
      - `/workflows/` (automation specs, flow diagrams)
      - `/access/` (credentials in 1Password, not plain text)
      - `/reports/` (monthly reports, call notes)
  - **Tool:** Google Drive, Notion, or Dropbox (client gets shared access)

- [ ] **Backup & disaster recovery plan**
  - **Automated backups:** All Make.com scenarios exported weekly (JSON)
  - **Client data:** Backed up to separate cloud (not just in production tools)
  - **Restoration test:** Verify you can restore from backup (quarterly)
  - **Documentation:** "If Rick gets hit by bus" guide for someone to take over

---

## Phase 4: Sales & Marketing Foundation (Get Clients)

### Website & Online Presence

- [ ] **Website live with pricing page**
  - **Minimum:** Single-page site (pricing, services, contact form, testimonials)
  - **Tool:** Carrd ($19/year), Webflow (free), or Framer
  - **Must have:**
    - Clear value proposition ("AI automation for growth")
    - Three pricing tiers (Starter, Growth, Enterprise)
    - CTA: "Book discovery call" (Calendly link)
    - Social proof (even if placeholder: "Launching Soon - Join Waitlist")
  - **SEO basics:** Title tags, meta descriptions, Google Analytics

- [ ] **Domain purchased & DNS configured**
  - **Domain:** clawops.com (or whatever you chose)
  - **Registrar:** Namecheap, Google Domains, Cloudflare
  - **DNS:** Point to website, email (Google Workspace MX records)
  - **SSL:** HTTPS enabled (usually automatic with host)

- [ ] **Social media profiles created**
  - **Required:** LinkedIn (business page)
  - **Optional:** Twitter/X (easier for thought leadership), Reddit (u/RickClaw_Dev active)
  - **Profile:** Professional headshot, bio mentions ClawOps, link to website
  - **First posts:** "Launching ClawOps - AI automation agency" + behind-the-scenes

- [ ] **Google Business Profile claimed** (if applicable)
  - **When:** If targeting local businesses
  - **Setup:** Add address (or "service area"), hours, services, photos
  - **Benefit:** Shows in local search, builds credibility

### Proposal & Sales Materials

- [ ] **Proposal template created**
  - **Tool:** Google Docs, Notion, or PandaDoc (tracks opens)
  - **Structure:**
    - Cover (client logo, "Prepared for [Name]")
    - Problem statement (their pain points)
    - Solution (how you'll solve it)
    - Scope (specific deliverables, timeline)
    - Pricing (tier + optional add-ons)
    - Case studies (even if hypothetical for first client)
    - Next steps (sign SOW, pay invoice, kickoff date)
    - Terms (30-day money-back guarantee, cancellation policy)
  - **Format:** PDF, professional design (Canva template)

- [ ] **Discovery call script prepared**
  - **Agenda:**
    1. Intro (2 min): Your background, ClawOps mission
    2. Their story (10 min): Business, pain points, goals
    3. Deep dive (10 min): Specific workflows, tool stack, volume
    4. Solution fit (5 min): How you'd help, tier recommendation
    5. Next steps (3 min): Send proposal, answer questions
  - **Questions to ask:**
    - What takes most time in your day?
    - What marketing/ops tasks do you avoid because they're tedious?
    - What tools do you use? (CRM, email, social, etc.)
    - What's your monthly budget for automation?
    - When do you want to start?
  - **Qualification:** Are they decision-maker? Do they have budget? Timeline?

- [ ] **Case study / portfolio piece ready**
  - **Problem:** "First client = no case studies"
  - **Solution 1:** Create hypothetical case study ("How we'd help [industry]")
  - **Solution 2:** Do 1-2 free/cheap pilots (friends, network) for testimonials
  - **Solution 3:** Case study from YOUR automation (meta!)
  - **Format:** One-pager PDF or website page
  - **Include:** Before/after metrics, client quote (even if it's "I'd hire them")

### Lead Generation Setup

- [ ] **LinkedIn profile optimized for sales**
  - **Headline:** "Founder @ ClawOps | AI Automation for [Target Audience]"
  - **About section:** Your story, who you help, how to contact
  - **Featured:** Pin case study, website, pricing page
  - **Activity:** Post 3x/week (automation tips, behind-the-scenes, industry insights)

- [ ] **Outreach list created (50-100 prospects)**
  - **Criteria:** Target market (e.g., agencies, e-commerce, B2B SaaS)
  - **Sources:** LinkedIn, industry directories, past network
  - **Data:** Name, company, title, LinkedIn URL, pain point (guess)
  - **Tool:** Google Sheets or Airtable

- [ ] **Cold email template written**
  - **Subject:** "Quick question about [their company]'s [pain point]"
  - **Body (under 75 words):**
    - Noticed [specific thing about their company]
    - We help [companies like yours] [specific outcome]
    - Built AI automations that [result] (example: saved 10 hrs/week)
    - Worth a 15-min call?
    - [Calendly link]
  - **Tone:** Helpful, not salesy. Personalized (use their name, company).
  - **Test:** Send to 10 people, track open/reply rate (aim for 5% reply)

- [ ] **Referral incentive created**
  - **Offer:** $250 Stripe credit for every referral who signs (applied to their bill)
  - **How:** Email to network: "Launching ClawOps, help me find first clients, I'll pay you"
  - **Target:** People who know your work, trust you, have networks (former colleagues, friends in business)

