## Phase 5: Pre-Flight Checklist (Final Review)

### Day Before First Client Signs

- [ ] **Re-test payment links** (make sure nothing broke)
- [ ] **Review MSA & SOW** (one last time, no typos)
- [ ] **Check Stripe account** (no restrictions, payouts enabled)
- [ ] **Confirm Calendly availability** (no scheduling conflicts next 2 weeks)
- [ ] **Clear calendar for onboarding** (block 10-15 hours for first client)
- [ ] **Mentally prepare** (you're about to be a business owner, not just dreaming)

### Within 24 Hours of First Payment Received

- [ ] Send welcome email (immediately, automate this later)
- [ ] Schedule kickoff call (within 48 hours)
- [ ] Create client workspace (folder structure)
- [ ] Set up monitoring (check in on automations daily first week)
- [ ] Send thank you note (handwritten or personal video = memorable)

### Week 1 With First Client

- [ ] **Daily check-ins** (first week only, builds trust)
- [ ] **Document everything** (time spent, issues, what worked)
- [ ] **Ask for feedback** (mid-week: "How's it going? What can I improve?")
- [ ] **Start testimonial seed** ("If you're happy with progress, would you write a review later?")

---

## Red Flags: DO NOT Accept First Client If...

- [ ] Stripe account is restricted (resolve first)
- [ ] You don't have E&O insurance (you'll regret it)
- [ ] No contract template ready (verbal agreements = lawsuits)
- [ ] You're not confident you can deliver (better to wait and learn)
- [ ] Client refuses to sign contract (walk away)
- [ ] Client asks for "free trial" with no commitment (tire-kicker)
- [ ] You haven't tested payment flow (broken checkout = lost deal)

**Rule:** If any of Phase 1 (Legal & Financial) is incomplete, DO NOT PROCEED. Phase 2-5 can be rough, but Phase 1 is non-negotiable.

---

## Common Mistakes First-Time Agency Owners Make

### Mistake 1: Accepting First Client Before Ready
**Result:** Sloppy delivery, no contract, payment issues, bad review
**Fix:** Use this checklist (yes, all of it)

### Mistake 2: Undercharging to "Get First Client"
**Result:** Client expects low price forever, you resent the work, unsustainable
**Fix:** Charge your published rate ($500/mo minimum). Offer 20% "early adopter" discount max.

### Mistake 3: No Contract "Because It's a Friend"
**Result:** Scope creep, no payment, ruined friendship
**Fix:** Always use contract. "It protects both of us."

### Mistake 4: Overpromising in Sales Call
**Result:** Can't deliver, client angry, refund/lawsuit
**Fix:** Underpromise, overdeliver. Say "I'll try" not "I'll definitely."

### Mistake 5: Not Tracking Time
**Result:** No idea if client is profitable, burn out, can't hire
**Fix:** Use Toggl from day 1. Track every minute first 3 months.

### Mistake 6: Skipping Insurance
**Result:** Client sues, you pay out of pocket, business dies
**Fix:** Buy E&O insurance before first client. Non-negotiable.

### Mistake 7: No Onboarding Process
**Result:** Client confused, you're winging it, bad experience
**Fix:** Follow checklist, send welcome email, use templates.

### Mistake 8: Forgetting to Celebrate
**Result:** First client feels like "just the start" instead of milestone
**Fix:** When payment clears, pour a drink. You're a founder now.

